known keys (forward compatibility).\"\"\"\n49\t        ...\n50\t\n51\t    @classmethod\n52\t    def error_result(cls, url: str, error: str) -> \"ResolvedContent\":\n53\t        \"\"\"Factory for failed resolutions. text='', extraction_error=error, resolved_at=utcnow().\"\"\"\n54\t        ...\n55\t```\n56\t\n57\t**URL canonicalization** lives in `seed_storage/dedup.py` as `canonicalize_url(url: str) -> str`. Used for URL dedup key generation.\n58\t\n59\t```python\n60\tdef canonicalize_url(url: str) -> str:\n61\t    \"\"\"Normalize URL for dedup. Strips utm_*, fbclid, ref, si, t, s params.\n62\t    Lowercases scheme+host. Preserves path case. Sorts remaining query params.\n63\t    Removes trailing slash and fragment. Returns original on malformed input.\"\"\"\n64\t    ...\n65\t\n66\tdef url_hash(url: str) -> str:\n67\t    \"\"\"SHA256 hex digest of canonicalize_url(url).\"\"\"\n68\t    ...\n69\t```\n70\t\n71\t---\n72\t\n73\t### Module List\n74\t\n75\t| Module | Responsibility | Key Interface |\n76\t|--------|---------------|---------------|\n77\t| `enrichment/models.py` | Shared types: `ResolvedContent`, `ContentType` | Dataclass with `to_dict()`, `from_dict()`, `error_result()` |\n78\t| `config.py` | All configuration via pydantic-settings `Settings` class | `Settings` singleton with validators for credentials, providers, constants |\n79\t| `dedup.py` | Redis-backed dedup (messages + URLs) and URL canonicalization | `DedupStore.seen_or_mark(key) -> bool`, `canonicalize_url()`, `url_hash()` |\n80\t| `circuit_breaker.py` | Redis-backed per-service circuit breaker | `CircuitBreaker.record_success()`, `.record_failure()`, `.is_open() -> bool` |\n81\t| `cost_tracking.py` | Redis-backed daily LLM cost counter | `CostTracker.increment()`, `.is_budget_exceeded() -> bool`, `.is_warning_threshold() -> bool`, `.get_current_spend() -> float` |\n82\t| `rate_limiting.py` | Redis-backed sliding window rate limiter | `RateLimiter.allow() -> bool` |\n83\t| `notifications.py` | Fire-and-forget Discord webhook alerts with debounce | `send_alert(message, debounce_key=None)` — sync, never raises |\n84\t| `worker/dead_letters.py` | Dead-letter storage and replay logic | `dead_letter(task_name, payload, exc, retries)`, `list_dead_letters()`, `replay_one()`, `replay_all()` |\n85\t| `worker/replay.py` | CLI for dead-letter replay | `python -m seed_storage.worker.replay --list/--all/--one` |\n86\t| `enrichment/resolvers/base.py` | Abstract base for all content resolvers | `BaseResolver.can_handle(url) -> bool`, `async resolve(url) -> ResolvedContent` |\n87\t| `enrichment/resolvers/webpage.py` | trafilatura + readability-lxml fallback | Truncate at 8000 tokens |\n88\t| `enrichment/resolvers/youtube.py` | yt-dlp metadata + transcript extraction | Truncate transcript at 12000 tokens |\n89\t| `enrichment/resolvers/image.py` | Vision LLM description | Provider-agnostic via `VISION_PROVIDER` config |\n90\t| `enrichment/resolvers/pdf.py` | docling + unstructured fallback | Truncate at 10000 tokens |\n91\t| `enrichment/resolvers/github.py` | GitHub REST API metadata + README | Authenticated if `GITHUB_TOKEN` present |\n92\t| `enrichment/resolvers/video.py` | Download → ffmpeg → transcription | Temp file cleanup in `finally` block |\n93\t| `enrichment/resolvers/twitter.py` | **TODO stub** — returns `error_result()` | URL pattern matching only |\n94\t| `enrichment/resolvers/fallback.py` | Best-effort HTML extraction | Never raises |\n95\t| `enrichment/dispatcher.py` | Routes URLs to resolvers by priority order | `ContentDispatcher.dispatch(url) -> ResolvedContent` |\n96\t| `graphiti_client.py` | Graphiti singleton with provider branching + vision client | `get_graphiti() -> Graphiti`, `get_vision_client()` |\n97\t| `query/search.py` | Graphiti search wrapper | `async search(query, num_results=10) -> list[EntityEdge]` |\n98\t| `expansion/frontier.py` | Redis frontier operations (add, pick, remove, metadata) | `add_to_frontier()`, `pick_top()`, `remove_from_frontier()` |\n99\t| `expansion/policies.py` | Per-resolver depth policies and priority scoring | `compute_priority()`, `DEPTH_POLICIES` dict |\n100\t| `expansion/scanner.py` | Celery beat task: scan frontier, enqueue expansions | `scan_frontier()` task |\n101\t| `expansion/cli.py` | CLI wrapper for manual expansion | `python -m seed_storage.expansion.cli expand <url>` |\n102\t| `ingestion/bot.py` | Discord bot real-time ingestion | `raw_payload` → `enrich_message.delay()` + reaction pubsub |\n103\t| `ingestion/batch.py` | DiscordChatExporter JSON import | `raw_payload` → `enrich_message.delay()`, cap 5000/run |\n104\t| `worker/app.py` | Celery app + queue routing + beat schedule | Two queues: `raw_messages`, `graph_ingest` |\n105\t| `worker/tasks.py` | All Celery tasks: `enrich_message`, `ingest_episode`, `expand_from_frontier`, `scan_frontier` | Central integration point |\n106\t| `health.py` | HTTP health endpoint on :8080 | `GET /health` → 200/503 JSON |\n107\t| `smoke_test.py` | Post-deploy verification | `python -m seed_storage.smoke_test` |\n108\t| `scripts/query.py` | CLI query interface | `python scripts/query.py \"query\" --limit N` |\n109\t| `scripts/rollback.py` | Graph rollback by timestamp | `python scripts/rollback.py --after <timestamp>` |\n110\t\n111\t## Rules\n112\t\n113\t1. **Implement exactly what the spec says.** Every interface, type, and contract above is authoritative. Do not invent new interfaces.\n114\t2. **Only create files in your assignment.** Do not create or modify files owned by other agents.\n115\t3. **Import shared types from their canonical locations** (e.g., `from seed_storage.enrichment.models import ResolvedContent`). If the module doesn't exist yet, use a minimal inline stub with a comment `# STUB: provided by {other-agent}`.\n116\t4. **Write all files FIRST, then run tests.** Do not read the spec for 20 turns — start writing code immediately based on the spec excerpt above.\n117\t5. **Dockerfile rule:** If you own a Dockerfile, you MUST `COPY` all source code directories BEFORE running `pip install .` or any install command. `pip install .` reads pyproject.toml which references the package — the source must already be in the image. Correct order: COPY pyproject.toml → COPY source dirs → RUN pip install.\n118\t5b. **supervisord.conf rule:** If you own supervisord.conf, NEVER use `%(ENV_*)s` interpolation for optional env vars — supervisord crashes if the env var is not set. Hardcode default values directly (e.g., `--concurrency=2`).\n119\t6. **Run your tests before finishing.** Execute `uv run pytest {your test files} -v --tb=short` and fix any failures.\n120\t6b. **Celery async/sync rule:** Celery tasks run synchronously. If your task must call async code (e.g., graphiti client), bridge it with `asyncio.run()` at the task boundary. Never `await` inside a sync task, and never pass a coroutine wrapper as if it were a coroutine — call it first to get the coroutine object:\n121\t  ```python\n122\t  # CORRECT\n123\t  @app.task\n124\t  def enrich_message(source_id: str):\n125\t      asyncio.run(_do_async_work(source_id))\n126\t\n127\t  async def _do_async_work(source_id: str):\n128\t      client = GraphitiClient()\n129\t      await client.add_episode(...)\n130\t\n131\t  # WRONG — asyncio.run() needs a coroutine object, not a function\n132\t  # asyncio.run(_do_async_work)        ← TypeError: a coroutine was expected\n133\t  # asyncio.run(some_wrapper)          ← same error if wrapper isn't called\n134\t  ```\n135\t7. **Commit your work** when done: `git add -A && git commit -m \"forge: types-agent iteration 8\"`\n136\t\n137\t## What to implement\n138\t\n139\tImplement every function, class, and constant from the spec excerpt above. Write tests that cover the expected behaviors. If the spec excerpt is insufficient, read the full spec at `docs/PARALLEL-SPEC-v2.md` — but only the sections relevant to your agent.\n140\t\n141\tFor unit tests:\n142\t- Mock all external dependencies (Redis, Neo4j, HTTP, Disc